snippet.textDisplay: I have to disagree with your opinion on the X vs XT models bro. On paper what you're saying makes sense, but that's only if the price they are advertising was the actual price it sold for. Unfortunately it's not even close, as you can't find a XT cpu going for less than 20-25% markup. What do you get for that extra 1/4 of your savings? Maybe some gain, maybe no gain, maybe even a slight decline vs your current X model. If it was 5% more I could accept that, but 25% is huge anyway you cut it. I wish I could say 'I may or may not pay the extra 25%, you'll just have to commit before finding out'. My frustration is with AMD, not you of course, but I would appreciate if you made this more clear on future videos.
